What you need to know:

Department of Architecture and Building Science at the University of Nairobi started in the 1950s with severe gender disparities.In 2020, the department has 187 female students and 12 female lecturers.Prior to that, it was common to find classes with no female students, especially in the 1970s and 1980s.The first Kenyan female lecturer joined the department in 2008 as a tutorial fellow, breaking years of male prevalence.